== AGENT

Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)

== GOAL

To find new antibiotics

== DATA

Initially Atomic and Molecular features of 2500 drugs and natural compounds. Then library of 6000 molecules and following more than 107 million molecules from ZINC15 database. 

== METHODS

Reinforcement learning

== RESULTS

They were able to discover a molecule that displayed bactericidal activity against a wide phylogenetic spectrum of pathogens.

== ISSUES

== SCORE

8

== COMMENTS

These algorithms are of great help to discover new antibiotics that scientist did not even think of. It speeds up the researches and helps scientist to explore into dimensions that were never touched.

